<!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Sponsored Trade Folk promise to bring their skill at least to 1000 and always sell to guildmates at cost of materials.  This priviso is maintained even <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>after</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> the member exits the Sponsored roster.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Trade Funds</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
The Trade Skill Account is for the use of the Sponsored Trade Folk to aid in increaseing their skill, supplimenting <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>in a small way</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> their own self-funding.  How to manage the account's funds and how to allocate them is determined by a meeting of the Sponsored Trade Folk and the Guild Treasurer.  These meetings should be held at least twice a month or at the disgression/need of the Sponsored Trade Folk.  <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Should a conflict of interest present itself, a non-sponsored officer or other appointed member must preside the meetings.</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
Per the meeting of 6/12/02, incoming Treasury funds are now split 50/50 between the General Fund and the Trade Skill Account.<br>
